s, Reparaturcafés und Mülltauchen - untersucht Maria Grewe in einer vergleichend angelegten Ethnographie die kulturellen Strategien im Umgang mit Überfluss und Knappheit und prüft dabei, welchen Beitrag kulturanthropologische Forschung für den Nachhaltigkeitsdiskurs leisten kann.  aRecycling, upcycling, and the share economy: sharing and swapping or the repurposing of everyday objects has gained increased importance in our consumption-driven and disposable society - in swap parties, repair cafés or in dumpster diving. Based on the central actors in these exemplary fields, Maria Grewe uses a comparative ethnographic approach to examine the cultural strategies for dealing with abundance and scarcity. In doing so, she also considers the contribution that cultural-anthropological research can make to sustainability discourse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aConsumption (Economics)xSocial aspects. 0aDumpster diving. 0aRecycling (Waste, etc.)xSocial aspects. 0aScarcityxSocial aspects. 0aSustainable livingxSocial aspects. 4aKultur. 4aKulturanthropologie. 4aNachhaltigkeit. 4aRecycling. 4aShare Economy. 4aSoziale Bewegung. 4aSoziale Bewegungen. 4aUpcycling. 4aWandel. 4aWirtschaft. 4aZivilgesellschaft. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aChange.  aCivil Society.  aCultural Anthropology.  aCulture.  aEconomy.  aRecycling.  aShare Economy.  aSocial Movement.  aSocial Movements.  aSustainability.  aUpcycling.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2017z9783110548242oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839438